summary: This is my Arwen. Body options: 7Base BBP, 7 Base TBBP HDT, ADEC, ADEC TBBP, CBBE, CBBE TBBP, UNPB and UNPB BBP.
descriptionHtml:
[img]http://i.imgur.com/cUjlngk.png[/img]
[img]http://i.imgur.com/lybOGmv.jpg[/img]
[font=Georgia][size=4][b][i][color=Royalblue]This is my Arwen with 7Base TBBP HDT Body. Optional 7Base BBP, ADEC, ADEC TBBP, CBBE, CBBE TBBP, UNPB and UNPB BBP.[/color][/i][/b][/size][/font]

[font=Georgia][size=3][i][color=Skyblue]"For I am the daughter of Elrond. I shall not go with him when he departs to the Havens: for mine is the choice of Skyrim, and as she so have I chosen, both the sweet and the bitter."[/color][/i]

[i][color=Skyblue]Arwen was the Half-Elven daughter of Elrond and Celebrían. She was often called Arwen Undómiel or Evenstar.
Now she decided to go to Skyrim, in search of her beloved Aragorn.
Will she find him?[/color][/i][/size][/font]
[img]http://i.imgur.com/WmD7UPs.jpg[/img]

[i][font=Georgia][size=4][b][color=Cornflowerblue]This is a Standalone Mod, don't need nothing else[/color][/b][/size][/font][/i]

[size=3][b][i][color=Cornflowerblue]Locations:[/color][/i][/b][/size]

[font=Georgia][size=4][i][color=Royalblue]Arwen-Imperial-Combat Mage Elemental / Voice=FemaleEvenToned/Levl.40: [/color][/i]

[i][color=Royalblue]You find her in Whiterun/Dragonsreach[/color][/i][/size][/font]


[font=Georgia][size=4][b][i][color=Cornflowerblue]Does not replace anything in Game!![/color][/i]
[/b][/size][/font]

[font=Georgia][size=3][b][i][color=Cornflowerblue]Recommend:[/color][/i][/b][/size][/font]
[i][color=Royalblue][font=Georgia][size=4][b]For All BBP_TBBP Versions: These body options do have extra requirements refer to those mod pages if you need extra help
-NOTE: To run any BBP/TBBP-Body version Mod properly, you have to install a skeleton which supports BBP or TBBP such as XP32's XP32 Maximum Skeleton, which is what i have used. If not you'll get a crash at startup.
There are several skeleton/animation/package options out there to choose from.[/b][/size][/font]
[/color][/i]


[font=Georgia][size=3][b][i][color=Cornflowerblue]Manually Installation:[/color][/i][/b][/size][/font]
[font=Georgia][size=3][i][color=Royalblue]Copy the ESP, Meshes and Textures-Folder[/color][/i]
[i][color=Royalblue]and paste it in your Data- Folder,[/color][/i]
[i][color=Royalblue]and confirm to overwrite if you already[/color][/i]
[i][color=Royalblue]have a Meshes and Textures Folder there.[/color][/i][/size][/font]
